gobblin.writer.test

Class GobblinTestEventBusWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.writer.test.GobblinTestEventBusWriter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataWriter<Object>, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class GobblinTestEventBusWriter
extends Object
implements DataWriter<Object>
    This class is meant for automated testing of Gobblin job executions. It will write any object it receives to a Guava EventBus . Tests can subscribe to the event bus and monitor what records are being produced.

    By default, the class will use TestingEventBuses to create an EventBus with name ConfigurationKeys.WRITER_OUTPUT_DIR.

    Note that the EventBus instances are static (to simplify the sharing between writer and tests). It is responsibility of the test to make sure that names of those are unique to avoid cross- pollution between tests.
